Paper: hep-th/9708151

Date: 1997-08-28

Title: On redefinitions of variables in gauge field theory

Authors: S. M. Klishevich

Comments: 13 pages, Latex, no figures

Journal-ref: Teor.Mat.Fiz. 116 (1998) 248-264

In this paper, for massive fields of spins 2 and 3 with non-canonicalLagrangians, we build Hamiltonians and full systems of constraints and showthat the use of derivatives in a redefinition of fields can give rise to achange of number of physical degrees of freedom.